Stephen Culling is a professional rodeo contestant from Fort St. John, British Columbia, who has made a name for himself in the world of rodeo, particularly in steer wrestling. In 2023, he secured the No. 10 spot in the World along with his first National Finals Rodeo qualification.

Here you can follow Stephen Culling’s net worth, career earnings, career, biography, achievements, relationship status, and more.

About Stephen Culling

Stephen Culling was born in Fort St. John, British Columbia. His journey in rodeo began at a young age, and he quickly became an all-around cowboy, competing in multiple different events.

Early Career

Culling’s list of accolades started in his teenage years when he won the steer wrestling at the National High School Finals and Canadian High School Finals.

Professional Career

Stephen Culling is a professional rodeo contestant from Fort St. John, British Columbia, specializing in steer wrestling.

Some of his notable achievements include winning the steer wrestling at the National High School Finals and Canadian High School Finals, being the 2016 PRCA steer wrestling rookie of the year, and becoming the 2018 Canadian Finals Rodeo Average champion.

In 2023, Culling won the Lea Park Rodeo, and his career earnings reached $209,241.

He also secured the No. 10 spot in the World along with his first National Finals Rodeo qualification.

Stephen Culling’s Net Worth in 2023

As of 2023, Stephen Culling’s net worth is estimated to be $1 million.

He has accumulated $104,026 in PRCA earnings.

Career Earnings

In the 2023 regular season, Culling earned $104,026. His major regular season wins included Rodeo Houston ($9,250), Rodeo Austin (Texas) ($11,237), Calgary (Alberta, Canada) Stampede ($13,750), and Caldwell (Idaho) Night Rodeo ($9,995).

Personal Details

Girlfriend

As of 2023, Culling is reported to be single. The steer wrestler is focused on his career.

How Old is Stephen Culling?

He is 30 years old, as of 2023.

What is his nationality?

He is Canadian.

Career Highlights

  • Career earnings: $209,241
  • 2022 world standings place: 27th
  • 2022 earnings: $59,272
  • Won the Lea Park Rodeo (Marwayne, Alberta) (2023)

FAQs About Stephen Culling

What is Stephen Culling’s Net Worth?

$1 million as of 2023.

Where is he from?

Culling is from Fort St. John, British Columbia.

What events does he compete in?

He competes in steer wrestling, team roping, and tie-down roping.

When did he join the Professional Rodeo Cowboys Association (PRCA)?

2016.
